## Cross‑Problem Links & A7 Guard Summary
**What is A7 (from prior work):** A universal input‑guard pattern we developed in the **Voltage** project (and referenced alongside the guessing game). It standardizes input reads, type checks, range checks, buffer clearing, and EOF handling so the same guard can be reused across programs without edits.

**A7 (sketch/template – not applied to code here):**
```c
#include <ctype.h>
#include <stdio.h>

// Returns 1 on valid read into *out, else 0. Ensures buffer is cleared.
int read_int_guarded(const char *prompt, int minv, int maxv, int *out) {
    for (;;) {
        int ch; int n;
        if (prompt) printf("%s", prompt);
        n = scanf("%d", out);
        if (n == 1 && *out >= minv && *out <= maxv) {
            // clear trailing input to end of line
            while ((ch = getchar()) != '
' && ch != EOF) {}
            return 1;
        }
        // bad read: clear line and reprompt
        if (n != 1) {
            while ((ch = getchar()) != '
' && ch != EOF) {}
        }
        else { // type ok, range bad
            while ((ch = getchar()) != '
' && ch != EOF) {}
        }
        printf("error: enter an integer in [%d..%d]
", minv, maxv);
    }
}
```

